HEADWORD: Centumvir
<hw>Cen*tum"vir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Centumviri</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>centum</ets> hundred + <ets>Vir</ets> man.]</ety> <fld>(Rom.
Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a court of about one hundred judges chosen to
try civil suits. Under the empire the court was increased to 180, and
met usually in four sections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

